Sugar Cookies

1 egg
1 tsp vanilla
3/4 tsp salt
1/4 tsp almond extract

whisk together in small bowl

2 1/2 c ap flour
1/4 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda

whisk together in large bowl

1 c super fine sugar (or sugar processed in food processor)
16 tbsp unsalted butter, cut into 1/2" pieces, ice cold

process in food processor with sugar. add qet ingredients and process for 10 s. add flour, process for 30 s, until it comes together. dump onto work surface and knead until it comes together. split in half. using hands, spread out each half to 7x9" rectangle on sheet of parchment. top with another sheet of parchment, using rolling pin, roll or press out to 10x14" oval, 1/8" thick. stack sheets and put onto baking sheet and chill in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hr. peel off top layer and put back on, flip over and take top off and discard. cut out shapes and transfer to cookie sheets. can reroll dough, chill first. decorate - if using just sugar, put on before baking. bake at 300F on lower middle rack for 14-17 min, rotating halfway through. rest for 5 min before removing to cooling rack.
